\f0\fs24 \cf0 Voltage divider\
\
A voltage divider (or potential divider) is a simple, fundamental passive linear circuit that takes a higher input voltage and scales it down to a lower output voltage. It is one of the most widely used building blocks in electronics.Here is a comprehensive breakdown of how it works, the formula behind it, its limitations, and practical applications.How It WorksA basic voltage divider consists of two resistors connected in series across a voltage source.When an input voltage Vin is applied across the pair of resistors, a current flows through them. Because the resistors are in series, the same current passes through both. As this current moves through each resistor, a voltage drop occurs across them proportional to their resistance values. By tapping into the connection point between the two resistors, you can read a fraction of the total input voltage Vout}